issue.title: Let's get this online!
issue.body:
Awesome job again, guys. But let's get this hosted!

You might consider using [OpenShift](https://www.openshift.com/pricing/index.html) instead of Heroku. It's a similar service, but their free tier gives you more (your app will only sleep after 24 hours, not 30 minutes).

There's a guide on deploying Flask apps [here](https://developers.openshift.com/languages/python/flask.html), it basically boils down to:
- [ ] Get your dependencies sorted out and listed in a `requirements.txt`
- [ ] Install their `rhc` tool, run a couple commands and edit one file

The dependencies thing means you'll want to figure out the venv again. I'd recommend deleting it from the repository (venvs aren't supposed to be shared like that) and starting a new one. It _should_ (fingers crossed) be as simple as

```
$ virtualenv create venv
$ source venv/bin/activate
$ pip install beautifulsoup4
$ pip install flask
$ pip freeze > requirements.txt
```

Let me know if you need anything!
